Plan: Linear Boot Sequence Refactor                                                                                                                                                     

 Context

 The current boot sequence spawns wifi_and_webserver_task as a concurrent FreeRTOS task immediately after hardware init, so Wi-Fi, webserver, and emulator start racing each other. The  
 user wants a fully linear sequence (no concurrent work before the emulator task starts) that matches a specific 16-step order and adds a "wait for WebSocket keyboard" step before the  
 beep.

 Target Boot Sequence

 1.  expander_init()
 2.  display_init()
 3.  display_boot_test()          ← splash, no beep yet (audio not up)
 4.  esp_psram_init()
 5.  mountSPIFFS()
 6.  wifi_prov_start() + wifi_prov_wait_for_ip(15000) inline — BLE fallback on timeout
 7.  stat(ROM_FILE)               ← abort if missing
 8.  new SpectrumHardware()
 9.  spectrum->loadROM() + reset()
 10. webserver_ensure_started()   ← only if Wi-Fi connected
 11. input_init()
 12. audio_init()
 13. webserver_wait_for_ws_client(timeout_ms)  ← only if Wi-Fi connected
 14. audio_play_tone(880, 120)    ← beep
 15. xTaskCreatePinnedToCore(emulator_task, ...)
 16. idle loop

